Deploy a Marketing Cloud Engagement Bundle to a Data Space

Add Marketing Cloud Engagement data to a Data Cloud data space based on the mapping.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Available in: Lightning Experience


USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To deploy a Marketing Cloud Engagement bundle:	Data Cloud for Marketing Data Aware Specialist permission set
In Data Cloud, go to the Data Streams tab, and click New.
Select Marketing Cloud, and click Next.
Select a data space for each business unit. Business unit to data space mapping is applicable only for bundles.

Each business unit must be mapped to at least one data space, and you can map a business unit to multiple data spaces. You can also map a data space to many business units.

If Allow Profile Business Unit Mapping Data is enabled in Engagement setup, make sure that the Engagement subscribers are mapped to the same business unit ingested into Data Cloud. If the SFMC Subscribers BU mapping data stream is empty, applications like Data Explorer, Segmentation, and Activation don’t get data for Individual and contact point DMOs.

Click Next.
Select a standard Engagement data bundle, and click Next.
Optionally edit labels or add formula fields.
Click Deploy.
If you’re ingesting a new business unit, you must deploy the data streams again.
